WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.990 --> 00:00:03.890
SANDY LEGER: Hi, friends.

00:00:03.890 --> 00:00:06.050
Thank you for coming here.

00:00:06.050 --> 00:00:10.880
Thanks for wanting to listen
to us and learn about

00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:13.720
prevention of human trafficking

00:00:13.720 --> 00:00:18.150
in the US and abroad.

00:00:18.150 --> 00:00:19.900
My name's Sandy Leger.

00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:25.350
I am the co-founder, president,
and chairman of

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:26.965
abolishslavery.org.

00:00:26.965 --> 00:00:31.130
And in a moment I'm going to
introduce Aaron Cohen here.

00:00:31.130 --> 00:00:32.390
He's our speaker.

00:00:32.390 --> 00:00:34.310
Human rights activist.

00:00:34.310 --> 00:00:37.200
But before I do that, I want to
tell you a little bit about

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:42.840
our organization and the
movement to free slaves.

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:46.130
Slavery has changed
over the years.

00:00:46.130 --> 00:00:51.120
It certainly wasn't abolished
150 years ago with the

00:00:51.120 --> 00:00:56.420
Emancipation Proclamation
with Abe Lincoln.

00:00:56.420 --> 00:00:59.620
As our president today says,
human trafficking is

00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:01.880
modern-day slavery.

00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:06.330
At Abolish Slavery, we work
to prevent the spread of

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:11.120
modern-day slavery by helping
establish and mentor human

00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:13.530
trafficking task forces
domestically and

00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:15.080
internationally.

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:17.070
That's a mouthful.

00:01:17.070 --> 00:01:20.970
These task forces find and
protect human trafficking

00:01:20.970 --> 00:01:23.930
victims and promote the
infrastructure needed to

00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:29.170
rescue victims and assist them
on the road to recovery.

00:01:29.170 --> 00:01:32.700
Today more than ever, victims of
human trafficking are being

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:40.830
prostituted, enslaved, abused,
tortured, and murdered by

00:01:40.830 --> 00:01:43.010
predators who exploit their
vulnerabilities.

00:01:45.550 --> 00:01:49.440
But with your help and with
the help of victim service

00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:55.810
providers, we can free the
captives together.

00:01:55.810 --> 00:01:59.950
The human trafficking movement
in the US is growing, and with

00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:05.170
it, many organizations are
training law enforcement to

00:02:05.170 --> 00:02:08.919
better understand the complex
dynamics of domestic

00:02:08.919 --> 00:02:11.270
prostitution and sex
trafficking.

00:02:11.270 --> 00:02:16.370
We recently completed a series
of investigations and rescues

00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:22.070
in New York, working with the
NYPD, and vice detective Chris

00:02:22.070 --> 00:02:28.010
Baughman from the Metro Las
Vegas Police Department and

00:02:28.010 --> 00:02:30.450
certified shelters.

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:41.720
These partnerships were the glue
that kept us together,

00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:46.630
and it led to the rescue
of several victims.

00:02:46.630 --> 00:02:49.600
One of these victims is a young
lady named Christina.

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:51.830
She's from New Hampshire.

00:02:51.830 --> 00:02:57.820
And I was there for all of
this, actually, as were

00:02:57.820 --> 00:02:59.790
Melissa and Gracie,
my daughter.

00:03:04.660 --> 00:03:08.110
She'd been trafficked all
throughout New Hampshire, all

00:03:08.110 --> 00:03:10.830
the way down to New York.

00:03:10.830 --> 00:03:14.050
And we rescued her-- it
was Abolish Slavery

00:03:14.050 --> 00:03:16.920
with the NYPD help.

00:03:16.920 --> 00:03:21.320
Her emotional reunion with her
mother was successful.

00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:24.130
And she's now seeing a
counselor, she's applying to

00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:29.530
colleges, and she has a blog
that you can visit at--

00:03:29.530 --> 00:03:30.926
what's the name of it?

00:03:30.926 --> 00:03:32.384
MELISSA GRACE HOON: It's on
coerciontofreedom.wordpress.com.

00:03:35.300 --> 00:03:38.077
SANDY LEGER: Coerciontofreedo
m.wordpress.com.

00:03:38.077 --> 00:03:38.514
MELISSA GRACE HOON: Correct.

00:03:38.514 --> 00:03:39.800
SANDY LEGER: Great.

00:03:39.800 --> 00:03:42.660
And her name's Christina.

00:03:42.660 --> 00:03:48.070
With us today, speaking of,
is the victim advocate for

00:03:48.070 --> 00:03:50.720
Abolish Slavery, Melissa
Grace Hoon.

00:03:50.720 --> 00:03:52.558
Could you stand up?

00:03:52.558 --> 00:03:53.808
MELISSA GRACE HOON: Hello.

00:03:57.450 --> 00:04:00.270
SANDY LEGER: It's Melissa's
responsibility to coordinate

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:03.390
survivor transition and
security, as she did with our

00:04:03.390 --> 00:04:07.710
survivor from New Hampshire,
so that post-rescue, our

00:04:07.710 --> 00:04:12.160
survivors receive the best care
possible from the service

00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:16.880
providers, and making sure that
their unique situations

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:22.450
are helped.

00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:26.660
As of late, we've been
increasingly using technology

00:04:26.660 --> 00:04:31.090
in our investigations and
finding sex trafficking

00:04:31.090 --> 00:04:33.190
victims online.

00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:39.190
We document them, and we're
allowed now to see something--

00:04:39.190 --> 00:04:41.540
I think Aaron's going to say
later-- something that was

00:04:41.540 --> 00:04:45.270
invisible, that we don't
normally know about, to

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:46.520
something that is visible.

00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:52.930
For the last two years, Abolish
Slavery has trained

00:04:52.930 --> 00:04:56.570
law enforcement in human
trafficking investigations in

00:04:56.570 --> 00:05:02.225
Thailand, Cambodia, Indonesia,
Haiti, Mexico--

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:08.540
Ooh.

00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:09.530
Wow, OK.

00:05:09.530 --> 00:05:13.260
That's like being in a
department store when you see

00:05:13.260 --> 00:05:14.510
yourself on the camera.

00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:23.300
And also in the US, with
the FBI's help.

00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.030
We plan to begin our
next round of

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:28.090
investigations next month.

00:05:28.090 --> 00:05:33.290
We don't know exactly where
we're going to be, because we

00:05:33.290 --> 00:05:34.590
had to change a plan.

00:05:34.590 --> 00:05:39.810
The victims actually moved, the
traffickers moved them, so

00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:44.350
it's not going to be where
we had intended in Texas.

00:05:44.350 --> 00:05:46.580
But we continue to work with law
enforcement when we do the

00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:50.900
investigations and the rescues
and transition the victims

00:05:50.900 --> 00:05:55.420
from a life of slavery
to a life of freedom.

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:58.350
We just take it so
for granted.

00:05:58.350 --> 00:06:02.090
We're also working on our next
installment of books and

00:06:02.090 --> 00:06:05.190
television production.

00:06:05.190 --> 00:06:09.980
We're excited to develop some
PSAs and other media to raise

00:06:09.980 --> 00:06:14.760
awareness and to raise crucial
funds needed to continue the

00:06:14.760 --> 00:06:16.320
work of bringing freedom
to those who are

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:19.000
lost in modern slavery.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:23.020
It's my hope, and all of our
hope, that this short film

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:25.990
we're about to show you will
help explain the painstaking

00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:30.180
work of rescuing victims who
at this very moment are

00:06:30.180 --> 00:06:31.430
enslaved in the US.

00:06:46.660 --> 00:06:47.860
AARON COHEN NARRATING: Human
trafficking is the

00:06:47.860 --> 00:06:50.290
fastest-growing illegal
business.

00:06:50.290 --> 00:06:53.010
It's already passed arms sales,
and it's in a position

00:06:53.010 --> 00:06:54.260
to pass drug sales.

00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:06.650
Ever since the internet boom,
sex trafficking has been

00:07:06.650 --> 00:07:09.040
growing at an alarming rate.

00:07:09.040 --> 00:07:12.110
The massage parlors of Asia are
teeming with young human

00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:13.360
trafficking victims.

00:07:17.410 --> 00:07:20.600
I met Na while working
undercover in Cambodia.

00:07:20.600 --> 00:07:22.810
She told me she was 19,
but I could see

00:07:22.810 --> 00:07:24.316
she was much younger.

00:07:24.316 --> 00:07:25.250
AARON COHEN: What?

00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:26.500
You're so shy.

00:07:29.570 --> 00:07:32.370
We're moving into the
hot zone right now.

00:07:32.370 --> 00:07:33.210
We're now literally
three buildings

00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:34.460
away from the retrieval.

00:07:37.575 --> 00:07:43.310
[MEN SHOUTING]

00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:45.390
AARON COHEN NARRATING: I would
rank Cambodia as one of the

00:07:45.390 --> 00:07:49.385
worst places for sex
trafficking.

00:07:49.385 --> 00:07:51.445
AARON COHEN: So we're getting
ready for the SWAT guy to come

00:07:51.445 --> 00:07:52.830
out of the station.

00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:56.030
Basic estimates suggest that
there's up to 27 million

00:07:56.030 --> 00:07:57.620
slaves in the world today.

00:07:57.620 --> 00:07:59.530
Here in Haiti, there's
an unprecedented

00:07:59.530 --> 00:08:02.430
300,000 domestic slaves.

00:08:02.430 --> 00:08:03.860
I look and I see some
of the children

00:08:03.860 --> 00:08:04.990
carrying in the street.

00:08:04.990 --> 00:08:07.810
I can't help but feel as if
we're looking at modern-day

00:08:07.810 --> 00:08:11.460
slavery here in Haiti.

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:13.600
AARON COHEN NARRATING: The
ancient land of Kush, known

00:08:13.600 --> 00:08:17.970
today as Sudan, was connected
to Egypt by the Nile River.

00:08:17.970 --> 00:08:21.620
Tradesmen and camel caravans
waged bloody civil wars for

00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:24.880
the past centuries over the
natural resources, leaving

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:28.230
African tribal communities
destitute.

00:08:28.230 --> 00:08:30.920
Heartbroken parents were facing
an agonizing choice

00:08:30.920 --> 00:08:33.730
when they discovered that their
children had been taken

00:08:33.730 --> 00:08:37.470
to this little-known place
called Darfur.

00:08:37.470 --> 00:08:41.120
It was a long, difficult journey
for the former slaves

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:44.120
to walk home hundreds of
miles across the front

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:47.710
lines of a civil war.

00:08:47.710 --> 00:08:49.130
MALE SPEAKER:
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:49.790
AARON COHEN: Silence.

00:08:49.790 --> 00:08:51.570
But I think they're starting to

00:08:51.570 --> 00:08:53.916
figure out what's happening.

00:08:53.916 --> 00:08:55.100
MALE SPEAKER: So nobody
should be afraid.

00:08:55.100 --> 00:08:56.660
It's going to be a good day.

00:08:56.660 --> 00:08:57.840
It's a happy day.

00:08:57.840 --> 00:09:01.680
And that very soon, you'll all
be able to go back to your

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:05.846
homes and to find your mothers
and fathers and your husbands

00:09:05.846 --> 00:09:08.231
and other relatives
and friends.

00:09:08.231 --> 00:09:12.240
[SHOUTING]

00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:14.166
AARON COHEN: This
is the children.

00:09:14.166 --> 00:09:17.960
They are running off here to be

00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:21.145
reunited with their families.

00:09:21.145 --> 00:09:23.109
They're very excited.

00:09:23.109 --> 00:09:31.456
[SHOUTING AND LAUGHTER]

00:09:31.456 --> 00:09:33.911
AARON COHEN: They're
very happy.

00:09:33.911 --> 00:09:36.857
Families are being reunited.

00:09:36.857 --> 00:09:40.270
These are the children that
were just released.

00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:43.431
There's pandemonium breaking
out as they hug each other

00:09:43.431 --> 00:09:45.636
that they're free.

00:09:45.636 --> 00:09:49.400
All of them have been abused
and have suffered many

00:09:49.400 --> 00:09:50.530
terrible things.

00:09:50.530 --> 00:09:52.506
They're very excited.

00:09:52.506 --> 00:09:56.680
You see joy breaking
out everywhere.

00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.656
AARON COHEN: Today's
your day, man.

00:09:58.656 --> 00:09:59.980
MALE SPEAKER:
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:09:59.980 --> 00:10:00.451
AARON COHEN: Right?

00:10:00.451 --> 00:10:01.701
Right.

00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:11.210
Hey, buddy, let me hold
this stuff for you.

00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:13.350
AARON COHEN NARRATING: When
Arason's mother unwittingly

00:10:13.350 --> 00:10:17.050
turned him over to his aunt, he
was brokered into domestic

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:21.490
slavery, forced to work 14 hours
a day and beaten if he

00:10:21.490 --> 00:10:22.860
do not obey.

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:26.550
He hadn't seen his mother
in more than 10 years.

00:10:26.550 --> 00:10:32.650
So at the age of 12, Arason
returned home and was reunited

00:10:32.650 --> 00:10:33.900
with his mother.

00:10:58.140 --> 00:11:00.070
[SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:11:00.070 --> 00:11:01.370
AARON COHEN NARRATING: This
is a serious business.

00:11:01.370 --> 00:11:03.082
It is very dangerous
to do this work.

00:11:03.082 --> 00:11:03.986
Hello, hello.

00:11:03.986 --> 00:11:05.342
[SHOUTING]

00:11:05.342 --> 00:11:07.265
AARON COHEN: It's OK, it's OK.

00:11:07.265 --> 00:11:10.100
It came back from the Human
Trafficking division that she

00:11:10.100 --> 00:11:13.450
was a legal adult, that the
documents were in order.

00:11:13.450 --> 00:11:14.660
The tape says it all.

00:11:14.660 --> 00:11:16.350
The truth is the truth.

00:11:16.350 --> 00:11:19.810
And no matter how hard you take
the truth and try to make

00:11:19.810 --> 00:11:22.390
it something else, it's
still the truth.

00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:24.230
They're not always
happy endings.

00:11:27.260 --> 00:11:31.820
Right in there is
our little girl.

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:34.390
Right now, the girls are
probably still sleeping.

00:11:34.390 --> 00:11:37.560
You can help some people, but
inevitably, the one you leave

00:11:37.560 --> 00:11:40.900
behind becomes so much more
prominent in your mind than

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:42.210
the ones that you can help.

00:11:42.210 --> 00:11:44.600
And that's something
I always live with.

00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:47.840
I always live with the fact--
people say, well how many

00:11:47.840 --> 00:11:48.730
children have you rescued?

00:11:48.730 --> 00:11:50.830
Or how many slaves
have you freed?

00:11:50.830 --> 00:11:55.360
And the answer is, how many have
I left behind, really?

00:11:55.360 --> 00:11:57.070
And that haunts me.

00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:58.440
It stays with me.

00:11:58.440 --> 00:11:59.690
It never leaves.

00:12:19.980 --> 00:12:25.350
SANDY LEGER: I've only watched
that a few times, and the boy

00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:28.290
who was two years old when they
took him-- and I have a

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.190
two-year-old.

00:12:30.190 --> 00:12:34.735
He can't even make real
sentences yet.

00:12:34.735 --> 00:12:37.000
I can't even imagine.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:40.910
OK, so it gives me great
pleasure to introduce to you

00:12:40.910 --> 00:12:42.160
Aaron Cohen.

00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:49.570
He's the mission director
for Abolish Slavery.

00:12:49.570 --> 00:12:50.430
He's an award-winning--

00:12:50.430 --> 00:12:52.320
I'll give you all the
goodies about him.

00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:57.240
He's an award-winning writer and
human rights activist who

00:12:57.240 --> 00:13:01.660
draws his inspiration from the
Jubilee, which is an ancient

00:13:01.660 --> 00:13:07.450
law of debt forgiveness and
setting the slaves free.

00:13:07.450 --> 00:13:16.140
Media, including FOX, CNN,
"Larry King Live," MSNBC, and

00:13:16.140 --> 00:13:19.280
NBC, have a lauded Aaron's work
in finding and rescuing

00:13:19.280 --> 00:13:22.610
victims of human trafficking.

00:13:22.610 --> 00:13:25.680
He was awarded the US
Congressional Certificate of

00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:34.200
Merit, the Prize for Humanity,
and the Major League

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:39.190
Baseball's Greatest Save
trophy for his efforts

00:13:39.190 --> 00:13:42.015
combating slavery in the
United States and

00:13:42.015 --> 00:13:44.810
in dozens of countries.

00:13:44.810 --> 00:13:48.420
Working with the Abolish Slavery
team, Aaron trains

00:13:48.420 --> 00:13:51.920
counter-human-trafficking task
forces and undercover police

00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:56.240
officers in the US and
other countries.

00:13:56.240 --> 00:14:02.090
His memoir, "Slave Hunter: One
Man's Global Quest to Free

00:14:02.090 --> 00:14:05.780
Victims of Human Trafficking,"
has been translated into many

00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:08.730
languages and will be available
at the book table

00:14:08.730 --> 00:14:11.700
following our presentation.

00:14:11.700 --> 00:14:16.540
Melissa and I and Gracie will
also be at the table, if any

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:20.930
of you are interested in making
a donation or asking us

00:14:20.930 --> 00:14:26.610
about how you can be involved,
how you can help, and how you

00:14:26.610 --> 00:14:31.820
can be part of setting
these slaves free.

00:14:31.820 --> 00:14:37.200
So without further to-do,
I give you Aaron Cohen.

00:14:37.200 --> 00:14:40.640
[APPLAUSE]

00:14:40.640 --> 00:14:43.590
AARON COHEN: Thank you.

00:14:43.590 --> 00:14:46.150
How is everybody today?

00:14:46.150 --> 00:14:49.700
I'm so excited to be here and to
talk to you about slavery.

00:14:49.700 --> 00:14:52.940
The original topic for the
discussion sort of germinated

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:55.990
when my friend Michael P. Hale
from Google and I were talking

00:14:55.990 --> 00:15:00.060
about the use of technology
in saving lives.

00:15:00.060 --> 00:15:04.170
And so we together came up with
this idea to sort of do a

00:15:04.170 --> 00:15:07.670
little study, a little bit of
investigation about how the

00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:11.590
role of technology is changing
both human trafficking

00:15:11.590 --> 00:15:13.780
tremendously but also
human existence.

00:15:13.780 --> 00:15:16.630
So if we're going to talk about
the role of technology

00:15:16.630 --> 00:15:20.291
in saving lives, two things
need to be defined first.

00:15:20.291 --> 00:15:23.170
First of all, we have to
define technology.

00:15:23.170 --> 00:15:24.520
What is technology?

00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:26.220
Where does it begin?

00:15:26.220 --> 00:15:28.790
Who were the originators
of technology?

00:15:28.790 --> 00:15:31.810
And secondly, we have
to define life.

00:15:31.810 --> 00:15:32.760
How does life begin?

00:15:32.760 --> 00:15:33.900
What is life?

00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:36.900
So what was really interesting
for me is you know, I'm a

00:15:36.900 --> 00:15:39.130
human rights activist and I
travel around the world,

00:15:39.130 --> 00:15:41.000
working with vice detectives.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:44.690
We work in task forces trying
to find victims of human

00:15:44.690 --> 00:15:46.110
trafficking.

00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:48.990
And it can be pretty
dry at times.

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:51.040
It's your typical scene,
drinking coffee and eating

00:15:51.040 --> 00:15:53.520
doughnuts, and most of the
time, waiting around.

00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:56.160
So I got really excited when
Michael talked to me about

00:15:56.160 --> 00:15:58.760
putting this speech together,
because I learned a lot of

00:15:58.760 --> 00:16:01.590
things studying about
technology.

