It went from a shirt to here,
and then I had to have a

00:29:35.490 --> 00:29:38.080
backpack to pick
up the signal.

00:29:38.080 --> 00:29:41.580
And I used to get such anxiety
over the wire.

00:29:41.580 --> 00:29:43.760
I would come into my hotel room
and it'd be sitting there

00:29:43.760 --> 00:29:46.890
on the counter, and my heart
would start racing.

00:29:46.890 --> 00:29:48.830
Oh my gosh, the wire.

00:29:48.830 --> 00:29:53.470
I would get very, very nervous
that somehow I would get

00:29:53.470 --> 00:29:56.180
caught wearing the wire and
something bad would happen.

00:29:56.180 --> 00:30:01.810
And so I began to project from
that thinking, I began to

00:30:01.810 --> 00:30:04.540
project fear onto the device.

00:30:04.540 --> 00:30:09.240
And what I had done was I had
put a reminder of fear in

00:30:09.240 --> 00:30:13.920
front of myself, and it began to
inhibit my ability to work

00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:15.100
with the victim in the room.

00:30:15.100 --> 00:30:18.140
And what I do when I enter that
room is I'm trying to get

00:30:18.140 --> 00:30:20.710
to know the person and
win their trust.

00:30:20.710 --> 00:30:25.120
But if I'm afraid, if I'm filled
with doubt, how am I

00:30:25.120 --> 00:30:26.700
going to do that?

00:30:26.700 --> 00:30:29.530
It's very difficult to win
someone's trust if you're

00:30:29.530 --> 00:30:30.720
doubtful and you're fearing.

00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:31.620
And I meditated on it.

00:30:31.620 --> 00:30:34.750
I thought to myself, you know,
I've got to put the wire away.

00:30:34.750 --> 00:30:38.740
I cannot work with the wire and
have it out and see it and

00:30:38.740 --> 00:30:41.610
have my heart started beating
as a reaction, almost like a

00:30:41.610 --> 00:30:44.090
Pavlov's dog reaction.

00:30:44.090 --> 00:30:47.240
I ring the bell and the dog
would think dinner's coming.

00:30:47.240 --> 00:30:50.640
Well, I would see the wire and
I would become fearful.

00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:55.830
And what I realized is that I
needed to keep the vision of

00:30:55.830 --> 00:30:58.830
what I was trying to do in front
of me, not the fear.

00:30:58.830 --> 00:31:02.625
So I had put a vision of
something that created fear

00:31:02.625 --> 00:31:05.680
and doubt in front of me, and it
was affecting the way that

00:31:05.680 --> 00:31:07.480
I performed in my job.

00:31:07.480 --> 00:31:09.730
So what I did instead
is I looked for an

00:31:09.730 --> 00:31:11.630
alternative to the wire.

00:31:11.630 --> 00:31:13.070
And it's interesting--

00:31:13.070 --> 00:31:17.770
you laugh about it, but these
birds, says it's a bit freaky

00:31:17.770 --> 00:31:19.370
with the wireless technology.

00:31:19.370 --> 00:31:22.100
They're just hanging on nothing
there in the air.

00:31:22.100 --> 00:31:23.940
And that's what I
was looking for.

00:31:23.940 --> 00:31:26.950
I was looking to become the
person that could work in that

00:31:26.950 --> 00:31:31.060
room with the victims in a way
where I wouldn't be caught

00:31:31.060 --> 00:31:33.820
wearing a wire and get
beat up or worse.

00:31:33.820 --> 00:31:37.930
So as time went on, I realized
I needed to put something in

00:31:37.930 --> 00:31:38.630
front of me.

00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:40.780
I needed to keep my vision
in front of me.

00:31:40.780 --> 00:31:44.900
And what I began to do is I
looked at the wire, and

00:31:44.900 --> 00:31:46.310
instead of having the
wire there, I

00:31:46.310 --> 00:31:48.080
replaced it with a key.

00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:51.240
And I put a key there on the
counter in front of me.

00:31:51.240 --> 00:31:52.890
And that made a huge
difference for me.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:56.610
Because when I would walk by and
see my keys there, all of

00:31:56.610 --> 00:31:59.330
a sudden, I would realize, oh,
yeah, I put the keys there,

00:31:59.330 --> 00:32:01.310
because the wire was
there before.

00:32:01.310 --> 00:32:05.020
And the key is this thing that
will unlock these victims from

00:32:05.020 --> 00:32:06.050
being enslaved.

00:32:06.050 --> 00:32:07.240
Even myself--

00:32:07.240 --> 00:32:11.070
I can unlock my own issues,
my own problems.

00:32:11.070 --> 00:32:13.210
Because I was doubting myself.

00:32:13.210 --> 00:32:17.440
I thought, why should I be
the guy to be doing this?

00:32:17.440 --> 00:32:19.860
How did I end up here?

00:32:19.860 --> 00:32:21.850
How could I possibly
sustain this?

00:32:21.850 --> 00:32:23.220
It's so expensive.

00:32:23.220 --> 00:32:27.460
All of these doubts and things
arised in my mind that

00:32:27.460 --> 00:32:30.380
probably could have changed
my path so that I

00:32:30.380 --> 00:32:32.280
wouldn't have continued.

00:32:32.280 --> 00:32:35.800
But I began to realize that not
only was the technology

00:32:35.800 --> 00:32:40.670
this great macro Big-Bang
phenomenon, but the technology

00:32:40.670 --> 00:32:43.130
was also this micro thing
inside of me.

00:32:43.130 --> 00:32:46.330
It was a micro/macro situation,
where both my life

00:32:46.330 --> 00:32:49.420
and the technology and the
application of them to freedom

00:32:49.420 --> 00:32:52.110
for others was something very
relevant to what was going on

00:32:52.110 --> 00:32:54.480
in my life.

00:32:54.480 --> 00:32:57.580
I discovered Dr. Masaru Emoto.

00:32:57.580 --> 00:33:00.190
Now he's a very controversial
figure in the scientific

00:33:00.190 --> 00:33:03.240
community, because he developed
a theory which sort

00:33:03.240 --> 00:33:05.790
of lends itself to what I'm
talking about right now.

00:33:05.790 --> 00:33:10.830
His idea was to take water,
dirty water from a dam, bring

00:33:10.830 --> 00:33:14.690
in a group of folks who could
meditate over the water, and

00:33:14.690 --> 00:33:17.620
then measure the molecules and
take pictures of the water

00:33:17.620 --> 00:33:20.530
crystals prior to the meditation
and then following

00:33:20.530 --> 00:33:21.960
the meditation.

00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:24.190
And he discovered some
shocking things.

00:33:24.190 --> 00:33:27.570
And if you look on the figure,
it shows the water from the

00:33:27.570 --> 00:33:33.800
dam, and then it shows the water
from the dam after the

00:33:33.800 --> 00:33:36.060
offering of a prayer.

00:33:36.060 --> 00:33:40.360
And he essentially photographed
water by putting

00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:42.670
love one water, thank you.

00:33:42.670 --> 00:33:45.410
And he began to notice that
whatever the messaging was,

00:33:45.410 --> 00:33:48.800
whatever the consciousness of
the people who were meditating

00:33:48.800 --> 00:33:51.940
over that water had, it
affected the molecular

00:33:51.940 --> 00:33:53.480
structure of the water.

00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:55.530
So he reduplicated
the experiment

00:33:55.530 --> 00:33:56.380
over and over again.

00:33:56.380 --> 00:33:58.880
He was criticized by the
scientific community for going

00:33:58.880 --> 00:34:02.070
straight to the public and not
debating this further in the

00:34:02.070 --> 00:34:02.950
scientific community.

00:34:02.950 --> 00:34:08.340
But whether or not you buy into
his theories or not, the

00:34:08.340 --> 00:34:13.510
idea that our conscious thoughts
affect us not only on

00:34:13.510 --> 00:34:16.010
a molecular level within
ourselves but the

00:34:16.010 --> 00:34:17.679
people around us.

00:34:17.679 --> 00:34:21.360
And what I began to realize was
that I was talking myself

00:34:21.360 --> 00:34:25.560
out of successfully rescuing
girls out of this life.

00:34:25.560 --> 00:34:29.350
And what I was talking myself
into by projecting fear, by

00:34:29.350 --> 00:34:33.940
projecting doubt, I was
literally manifesting that.

00:34:33.940 --> 00:34:38.330
I was manifesting getting
caught wearing a wire.

00:34:38.330 --> 00:34:39.699
And it's a very dramatic
scene.

00:34:39.699 --> 00:34:43.409
They rip the wire from you, and
then they smash it, and

00:34:43.409 --> 00:34:44.540
then the next thing
you know, there's

00:34:44.540 --> 00:34:45.650
three guys at the door.

00:34:45.650 --> 00:34:49.254
And your hair, and this and
that, and do I fight back?

00:34:49.254 --> 00:34:53.179
And so all of that was something
that I was able to

00:34:53.179 --> 00:34:56.290
actually manifest through
my fear of it.

00:34:56.290 --> 00:34:58.680
And I had to change
my thinking.

00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:02.010
So when I found the water
molecule study, I realized

00:35:02.010 --> 00:35:06.520
that if I create positive
affirmations for myself, if I

00:35:06.520 --> 00:35:10.720
have a can-do attitude instead
of a "oh my gosh, what will

00:35:10.720 --> 00:35:14.800
happen if that happens?"
attitude, I needed people to

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:16.820
speak favor over me.

00:35:16.820 --> 00:35:20.150
I was out there maybe a little
bit too much on my own, and I

00:35:20.150 --> 00:35:24.070
began to doubt and fear.

00:35:24.070 --> 00:35:29.340
Another analogy that helped
me was the idea that I had

00:35:29.340 --> 00:35:31.840
reached a point where I was
crawling in this movement.

00:35:31.840 --> 00:35:34.150
I couldn't raise the funding.

00:35:34.150 --> 00:35:36.780
If I rescued a victim, I could
barely take care of that one

00:35:36.780 --> 00:35:38.390
particular person.

00:35:38.390 --> 00:35:39.930
I needed wings to fly.

00:35:39.930 --> 00:35:43.710
I needed to find out a way to
move from my caterpillar

00:35:43.710 --> 00:35:48.590
position into a position of
becoming a butterfly.

00:35:48.590 --> 00:35:52.000
And I did that by going to
graduate school and studying

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:53.350
the subject of the Jubilee.

00:35:53.350 --> 00:35:57.660
Now Jubilee was this ancient
musician who lived way back in

00:35:57.660 --> 00:36:01.450
ancient Sumeria nearly
5,000 years ago.

00:36:01.450 --> 00:36:03.780
He's called the father
of all musicians.

00:36:03.780 --> 00:36:06.730
But today, we still call a good
party after his name.

00:36:06.730 --> 00:36:08.750
We still use his
name, Jubilee.

00:36:08.750 --> 00:36:10.470
The queen has a 50-year
anniversary.

00:36:10.470 --> 00:36:11.740
It's the Jubilee.

00:36:11.740 --> 00:36:13.710
So I went to graduate school.

00:36:13.710 --> 00:36:17.440
I studied the agent law of the
Jubilee, which was found not

00:36:17.440 --> 00:36:20.480
only in biblical tradition
but in all the peripheral

00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:20.970
traditions.

00:36:20.970 --> 00:36:25.620
Because the musician Jubilee
himself was so ancient that we

00:36:25.620 --> 00:36:28.030
find Jubilee in Tibetan
Buddhism.

00:36:28.030 --> 00:36:31.370
We find Jubilee in Christianity
and Islam.

00:36:31.370 --> 00:36:34.080
It's in Judaism.

00:36:34.080 --> 00:36:35.600
It's in Hinduism.

00:36:35.600 --> 00:36:39.540
It's found cross-platform
amongst all societies.

00:36:39.540 --> 00:36:42.400
So I essentially
wrote a thesis.

00:36:42.400 --> 00:36:43.490
I wrote a book.

00:36:43.490 --> 00:36:45.160
I had a dream.

00:36:45.160 --> 00:36:48.640
And instead of approaching my
dream with fear, I began to

00:36:48.640 --> 00:36:51.300
put my vision in front of me.

00:36:51.300 --> 00:36:55.250
I had these little circles that
had chains broken, and

00:36:55.250 --> 00:36:56.430
I'd put it up over my bed.

00:36:56.430 --> 00:36:59.290
And I'd wake up in the morning
and I would see there the

00:36:59.290 --> 00:37:00.460
broken chains.

00:37:00.460 --> 00:37:02.210
And I would think to myself,
I'm going to do it.

00:37:02.210 --> 00:37:03.440
I'm going to do it.

00:37:03.440 --> 00:37:05.360
I would speak favor
over myself.

00:37:08.170 --> 00:37:12.340
At the time, I was working with
a rock band, and I found

00:37:12.340 --> 00:37:15.990
some incredible musicians
who would help me.

00:37:15.990 --> 00:37:17.950
And we traveled to
the G8 summits.

00:37:17.950 --> 00:37:20.590
We asked all the other musicians
we could find to

00:37:20.590 --> 00:37:24.250
sign petitions, and we set the
world record the biggest

00:37:24.250 --> 00:37:25.460
petition ever created.

00:37:25.460 --> 00:37:27.710
It was millions and millions
of signatures.

00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:31.880
And we submitted it at the G8
summit in 1999 to Bill Clinton

00:37:31.880 --> 00:37:36.100
and the political leaders to
drop Third World debt.

00:37:36.100 --> 00:37:38.190
And it was a huge success.

00:37:38.190 --> 00:37:41.670
So I had taken a few of the
little principles that I had,

00:37:41.670 --> 00:37:44.250
which was positive
affirmations--

00:37:44.250 --> 00:37:47.330
but not just positive
affirmations.

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:49.190
Changing my mindset.

00:37:49.190 --> 00:37:51.580
It's one thing to have
a positive mentality.

00:37:51.580 --> 00:37:55.150
It's another thing to say, I'm
going to be transformed by

00:37:55.150 --> 00:37:56.710
renewing my mind.

00:37:56.710 --> 00:37:58.980
So I began to try to think
of ways that I

00:37:58.980 --> 00:38:01.700
could renew my thinking.

00:38:01.700 --> 00:38:03.880
The campaign was
a huge success.

00:38:03.880 --> 00:38:05.810
Bono took the lead.

00:38:05.810 --> 00:38:09.870
Perry Farrell and Bob Geldof
were big supporters.

00:38:09.870 --> 00:38:13.190
We raised a lot of money
and we parlayed that.

00:38:13.190 --> 00:38:16.060
Now the Jubilee was forgiving
debts and freeing slaves, and

00:38:16.060 --> 00:38:18.030
I wanted to try to manifest
this in my life.

00:38:18.030 --> 00:38:21.040
So I sought out to first
forgive debts.

00:38:21.040 --> 00:38:22.590
And we forgave Third
World debt.

00:38:22.590 --> 00:38:25.560
We're still working today with
Rolling Jubilee that is an

00:38:25.560 --> 00:38:28.170
organization that works to
relieve medical debt for

00:38:28.170 --> 00:38:30.410
people who have fallen
into poverty.

00:38:30.410 --> 00:38:33.240
But the Jubilee was a
two-pronged thing-- forgiving

00:38:33.240 --> 00:38:36.260
debts and also freeing slaves.

00:38:36.260 --> 00:38:41.455
In 1997, when I was working with
Michael P. Hale, I didn't

00:38:41.455 --> 00:38:43.080
even know where slavery
existed.

00:38:43.080 --> 00:38:44.680
I just knew that theoretically,
it was

00:38:44.680 --> 00:38:48.090
something that I wanted to talk
about, the idea of being

00:38:48.090 --> 00:38:51.970
enslaved to myself, my own
thinking, or my ability to

00:38:51.970 --> 00:38:54.350
transform from that caterpillar
position to a

00:38:54.350 --> 00:38:56.780
butterfly and renew my mind.

00:38:56.780 --> 00:38:57.690
So what did we do?

00:38:57.690 --> 00:38:59.510
We went online.

00:38:59.510 --> 00:39:03.250
We used technology to find out
where there were slaves.

00:39:03.250 --> 00:39:06.040
So I essentially went into a
search engine and then I typed

00:39:06.040 --> 00:39:10.450
in slavery, and I began looking
at a few links, and I

00:39:10.450 --> 00:39:13.230
saw that there was
slavery in Sudan.

00:39:13.230 --> 00:39:19.160
So after we created a concert
tour, we did some festivals,

00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:22.000
we raised some money, and the
next think you know, I was on

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:25.060
a plane on my way to this
country, Sudan.

00:39:25.060 --> 00:39:28.940
Flying over the Nile River.

00:39:28.940 --> 00:39:32.720
Crossing the border of Kenya
into Sudan, there's this city

00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:35.650
called Lokichogio, and it's
sort of their last outpost

00:39:35.650 --> 00:39:38.190
before you're going all the
way inside, where there's

00:39:38.190 --> 00:39:39.930
really no more hospitals,
there's no more

00:39:39.930 --> 00:39:42.270
infrastructure, no more
Coca-Cola, no

00:39:42.270 --> 00:39:43.190
more bottled water.

00:39:43.190 --> 00:39:47.310
It's ceramic water filters
after this point.

00:39:47.310 --> 00:39:48.190
We land.

00:39:48.190 --> 00:39:50.540
The local military greets us.

00:39:50.540 --> 00:39:53.440
And at the time, I didn't really
know what I was getting

00:39:53.440 --> 00:39:54.450
myself into.

00:39:54.450 --> 00:39:58.530
I just knew that I wanted to be
involved in freeing slaves.

00:39:58.530 --> 00:40:02.340
And so we land and the reality
hadn't really hit me yet.

00:40:02.340 --> 00:40:03.930
I was sort living--

00:40:03.930 --> 00:40:07.420
it was kind of like "The Lion
King." The trees were similar.

00:40:07.420 --> 00:40:09.440
There was drum music playing.

00:40:09.440 --> 00:40:13.430
And I romanticized Africa so
much that when I landed, it

00:40:13.430 --> 00:40:16.820
hadn't really hit me what
was about to happen.

00:40:16.820 --> 00:40:21.270
So we're landing, the plane is
there, and they begin loading

00:40:21.270 --> 00:40:24.540
bodies into body bags to move
them on trucks out of the

00:40:24.540 --> 00:40:27.650
region, because the civil war
between the north and south

00:40:27.650 --> 00:40:29.060
was very bloody.

00:40:29.060 --> 00:40:33.540
And the Janjaweed, these
raiders, were being supported

00:40:33.540 --> 00:40:37.010
by this group nobody had ever
heard of called al-Qaeda.

00:40:37.010 --> 00:40:40.610
And al-Qaeda was there, and
they were then looking to

00:40:40.610 --> 00:40:44.560
subjugate people into slavery
to promote the well-being of

00:40:44.560 --> 00:40:46.720
some of their sponsors.

00:40:46.720 --> 00:40:50.920
So we would unload the survival
kits and deal with

00:40:50.920 --> 00:40:53.760
the murahaleen.

00:40:53.760 --> 00:40:55.870
We called them the Schindlers
of the Taliban.

00:40:55.870 --> 00:40:59.020
They were these humanitarian
Muslim guys who had helped to

00:40:59.020 --> 00:41:03.610
devise an Underground Railroad
in Sudan, bringing the victims

00:41:03.610 --> 00:41:05.890
out from the north, from
this place no one

00:41:05.890 --> 00:41:07.350
had ever heard of--

00:41:07.350 --> 00:41:09.650
Darfur.

00:41:09.650 --> 00:41:11.330
The slaves come out.

00:41:11.330 --> 00:41:15.610
You start to put a face on
slavery and to realize that a

00:41:15.610 --> 00:41:18.600
slave is not the same
as a free person.

00:41:18.600 --> 00:41:21.610
A free person is responsible
for all their decisions.

00:41:21.610 --> 00:41:24.700
Somebody who's a victim of
slavery, they have very little

00:41:24.700 --> 00:41:26.520
responsibility in their life.

00:41:26.520 --> 00:41:29.290
And so when you begin to see
this humble spirit--

00:41:29.290 --> 00:41:32.200
my first encounter with slaves
was really shocking, because

00:41:32.200 --> 00:41:35.600
they would just look down and
then they wouldn't give eye

00:41:35.600 --> 00:41:38.310
contact, and they would
just answer yes or no.

00:41:38.310 --> 00:41:39.560
They were very, very
submissive.

00:41:42.030 --> 00:41:44.440
Some of the children that we
encountered in the camps had

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:45.190
nothing at all.

00:41:45.190 --> 00:41:48.030
They had come back through the
Underground Railroad, and

00:41:48.030 --> 00:41:51.080
along the way, someone saw
shorts or a shirt, would take

00:41:51.080 --> 00:41:53.520
it from them.

00:41:53.520 --> 00:41:56.550
But ultimately, reuniting them
with their families after that

00:41:56.550 --> 00:41:59.430
arduous journey was an
incredible moment of my life.

00:41:59.430 --> 00:42:02.980
I realized something about
myself, that whatever dreams

00:42:02.980 --> 00:42:06.940
and goals that I had had before,
of having this big

00:42:06.940 --> 00:42:09.790
music festival or doing
these things,

00:42:09.790 --> 00:42:11.440
those dreams were fine.

00:42:11.440 --> 00:42:15.080
But the idea of liberating
people had superseded all my

00:42:15.080 --> 00:42:16.090
other plans.

00:42:16.090 --> 00:42:19.380
And it became sort of my master
dream for my life, the

00:42:19.380 --> 00:42:22.930
ability to take what I've been
given, the education that I'm

00:42:22.930 --> 00:42:27.240
